{
  "texts": [
    "In transfer, learning the aim is to improve the predictive function in a target domain using knowledge from a source domain.",
    "Or to put simply, infer information about the target by leveraging knowledge from the source domain.",
    "A domain is defined as D ¼ X, p X ð Þ f gcontaining X, a feature space and p X ð Þ, a marginal probability distribution.",
    "The assumption here is that the source and the target domains are not equal and/or that the source and target tasks are not equal.",
    "In domain adaptation, the aim is to improve the target predictive function by learning a mapping that reduces the discrepancies between the source and target distributions."
  ]
}